  "texts": [
    "Fundamentally, formative feedback or scaffolds can be employed to stimulate cognitively activating activities for students, thereby creating a dynamic and effective learning environment.",
    "Together, they encourage students to be active participants in their learning journey, fostering a deeper understanding and mastery of the subject matter.",
    "By integrating LLMs into learning platforms, one can leverage their ability to provide effective formative feedback.",
    "This approach promotes the advanced learning principle of SRL, thereby enriching the overall learning experience and leading to improved learning outcomes.",
    "LLMs have the potential to provide real-time formative feedback across all three dimensions of SRL-cognition, metacognition, and motivation-depending on the learners inputs and progress."
  ],
